                                                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="12427140" author="fuzzylogic" created="Thu, 10 Aug 2006 09:35:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Low hanging fruit for 10.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12427411" author="fuzzylogic" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2006 05:53:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Simple patch which moves derbyTesting.jar into a top-level test directory in the -bin, -lib, and -lib-debug distributions. Should we add java/testing/README.htm into the test directory as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12427525" author="djd" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2006 15:10:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds like a good idea to put the testing readme.&lt;br/&gt;
Could we also ship other jars there (in the test folder) that the harness requires, like the oro matcher stuff.  That&apos;s alv2 right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12427589" author="fuzzylogic" created="Fri, 11 Aug 2006 20:10:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, jakarta-oro-2.0.8.jar is ALv2, I&apos;ve added it and the testing readme to the test directory. Committed to trunk with revision 430864.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12427767" author="djd" created="Sun, 13 Aug 2006 17:56:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Download db-derby-10.2.1.0-bin.zip does not include a separate test folder so this bug is not fixed on 10.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12429840" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2006 00:46:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged to 10.2 branch in mega-merge, marking Resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12431934" author="djd" created="Thu, 31 Aug 2006 19:24:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The separation has made the tests impossible to run wihtut moving derbyTesting.jar back into the lib directory. I think the test separation is good and there are two items of work required to complete this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Change the harness and policy file to handle separate locations&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Have the buildjars target create a directory structure that mimics the layout in the distribution, ie. test and lib folders. This will lead to nightly and developer testing that mimics the distribution and how users will run it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will add sub-tasks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12435815" author="rhillegas" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2006 15:41:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 10.2.2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12458254" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 13 Dec 2006 19:57:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No current target fix version&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12913183" author="kmarsden" created="Tue, 21 Sep 2010 20:03:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4806&quot; title=&quot;SysinfoCPCheckTest fail on different Windows platforms on 10.6.2.0 release candidate &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-4806&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-4806&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is an example where  issues in the differences between the buildjars target and the distribution did not come  until the release candidate. It would be good to have derbyTesting.jar laid out the same for buildjars as it is for the distribution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
